Only negative I found was that there is no air conditioning and the heating is controlled for the whole floor.	It was a bit stuffy/hot because there is no air conditioning but it did have a nice fan that was sufficient.	Hotel has air conditioning in the lobby and the hallway, but rooms are cooled by opening the window to the Vancouver air and turining on the oscillating desk fan.	They provide a fan in the room but being very spoiled by air conditioning it was still HOT - not their fault.	Our stay was in August and yes even Vancouver gets hot weather the hotel nor any restaurant etc... have air conditioning so yes it was hot.